cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the design of incentive mechanisms for a blockchain-based platform, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also involves the study of token economics, which can be categorized under game theory (cs.GT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of systems modeling and simulation suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY) and the need to incentivize various stakeholders points towards social and information networks (cs.SI).
